properties.Name: AminoAcidMolecularFunction
properties.Description:
The molecular function(s) associated with the amino acid.

Ex:
Non-protein amino acids have important roles as metabolic intermediates, such as in the biosynthesis of the neurotransmitter gamma-amino-butyric acid (GABA). 

Many amino acids are used to synthesize other molecules, for example:

Ex:
-  Tryptophan is a precursor of the neurotransmitter serotonin. 
-  Glycine is a precursor of porphyrins such as heme. 
-  Arginine is a precursor of nitric oxide.

Columns.Name: AminoAcidId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an amino acid.

Columns.Name: ProteinMolecularFunctionTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a protein molecular function type.

Columns.Name: AminoAcidMolecularFunctionNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the amino acid molecular function.
